# WSL2 Environment Rules

These rules are binding for this repository.

## Shell and operating environment

- Use WSL2 / bash only for commands suggested to the user.
- Do not suggest PowerShell commands.
- Do not suggest `cmd.exe` commands.
- Do not suggest Windows batch syntax.
- If a tool, IDE, or metadata shows Windows-style paths, still write commands and paths for WSL/bash.

## Path style

Use repo-relative paths first.

If an absolute path is needed, use POSIX paths. The root of the project can be expressed as follows: 

Good:

```text
/home/sorin/WORK/Faculty/Teaching/00_UTILS/Python_english_course/
/mnt/c/Users/sorin/00_S_WORK/WORK/Faculty/Teaching/00_UTILS/Python_english_course/.cursor\rules\wsl-environment.mdc

```

Never use Windows drive/backslash paths in chat or generated instructions.

Bad:

```text
C:\Users\...
D:\...
methods\straight_woody\variants\base
```

If a rule conflicts with Windows path metadata from the IDE, these rules win.

## Python and pip commands

For every Python, pip, pytest, or script execution command in this repository, use the project conda environment first:

```bash
conda activate python312 && python ...
```

Examples:

```bash
conda activate python312 && python manager_scripts/create_method_template.py --method straight_woody --variant base --dry-run
```

```bash
conda activate python312 && python methods/straight_woody/variants/base/stdexec.py --mode train --config methods/straight_woody/variants/base/configs/train_TotalText_debug_cpu.json --project-root . --device cpu --dry-run
```

```bash
conda activate python312 && python -m pytest
```

Do not give bare `python ...`, `pip ...`, or `pytest ...` commands for this project unless explicitly instructed otherwise.

## Command style

Prefer direct, reproducible commands.

Avoid GUI/click instructions unless explicitly requested.

Keep commands bash-compatible.
